The accused, who was not named, was convicted of acts of terrorism, criminal association, murder, robbery, and illegal possession of firearms. The death penalty has not been applied in Mali since a moratorium on executions was put in place in 1980. In a statement, Minusma said this was the second time that specific attacks against its troops had been at the heart of a legal charge that has resulted in a trial and convictions The Minusma peacekeeping force, which has had 12 000 troops in Mali since 2013 is the UNâ€™s largest and deadliest operations. Peacekeepers are frequently killed or wounded in attacks by al-Qaeda and Islamic State fighters.  --BBC--